^cbbTHE STORY
	^c6fIn a time and place where chaos, violence, and crime were rampant, two brothers, 
Sartana and Pike, were renowned and feared. Born as twins in 1840, they had become 
the most sought after hired guns in the west by the time they were 20. Eventually, 
their reputation had earned the attention of civil war officers and between 1861 
and 1865, they fought for the Union. Together, they racked up quite the body count 
and both earned medals of honor for valor and devotion by the end of the war.

^P
^cbbTHE STORY 		(cont'd.)
	^c6fAfter the war, the two brothers made their living as bounty hunters. As the 
two further developed their reputation, Sartana noticed Pike slowly turning into 
someone he did not recognize. Pike became cruel and ruthless. He didn't just simply 
kill the men who had bounties on their heads; he would capture them, bind them, and 
torture them over long periods of time. Eventually, Pike changed his name to Devil 
Eyes; it was fitting given the fact that Pike enjoyed gazing deeply into the eyes 
of his victims as the life slowly left their bodies. 

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fSome years later, news about people being kidnapped in the dead of the night 
for unknown reasons spread like wildfire. The kidnappings were committed by a mysterious 
cult, led by a trio called The Unholy Trinity (Jilaiya: The Witch, Droge: The Warlock, 
and Zagan: The Antipope). Bounties were put in place for various cult members. The 
rewards were high, so high that Pike became greedy. He no longer wanted to split 
the rewards, which caused a rift between the two brothers. One night, while Sartana 
was sleeping, Pike went out on his own in search of the cult.

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fSartana awoke in shock, knowing that his brother had abandoned him. He was alone. 

	After a couple more years of lone bounty hunting, Sartana yearned for the quiet 
life and made way for North Carolina where much of his family lived at the time. 
During his trek, an enigmatic hooded lady, seeming to appear from thin air, approached 
him, claiming to have news of his brother's whereabouts. Sartana was convinced that 
the woman was lying until she tossed him Pike's prized Colt 45. He knew it was Pike's 
peacemaker because his initials were chiseled on the side of the gun. 

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fSartana asked the lady about Pike's location. She unraveled an ancient-looking 
map and pointed to an island, uncharted on any conventional map at the time, near 
the Bermuda Triangle. She called the place Isla de la Sombra (Island of the Shadow). 
She then gave Sartana directions on where to acquire a boat to get to the island. 
Sartana then asked the strange lady how she knew where to find him and how she knew 
about Pike. An impish grin crawled on her pallid face as she said, ^c4c"my master 
knows everything; and you and your brother both bear the mark."

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fSartana, confused, inquired about the mark. The woman pointed to the birth mark 
on the back of Sartana's neck and said, ^c4c"You two were destined to be his left 
and right hand." ^c6fShe then walked away. Sartana called for her, but his calls 
fell on deaf ears as the hooded lady disappeared into the pitch black night.
	Against his better judgment, Sartana decided to go find his brother. He headed south, 
amassing food and resources along the way, to the border of Georgia where he got 
the boat to get to Shadow Island.

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fAfter a few days of sailing, the boat crashed into a sandy shore in the middle 
of the night, waking Sartana from his slumber. He wasn’t sure if he had arrived at 
his destination or some random island. Regardless, he was weary from sailing and 
sought rest. 
	^c6fSartana moored his boat and stepped foot on the sandy shore, proceeding toward 
a vast forest in search of a suitable place to camp. As Sartana set up camp, robed 
hooligans emerged out of nowhere. He was surrounded. 

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fSartana instantly reached for his Colt, but before he could get a single shot 
off, he was knocked out by a massive blow to the back of the head. Sartana awoke 
the next night in a decrepit vacant room lit by candlelight, stripped of his weapons, 
bound to an altar, and encircled by dark hooded figures decked out in long voluminous 
robes as black as night. A tall handsome man in a dusty grey coat and an open crown 
hat upon his head appeared in the distance, slowly making his way toward Sartana. 
 It was Pike, except he was not the same.

^P
^cbbTHE STORY		(cont'd.)
	^c6fHis skin had an uncanny pallor and his eyes glinted like emeralds frozen in 
ice. Pike gazed upon his brother. A dire grin slowly formed on his face, revealing 
tiger-like teeth. Sartana, in a weak voice, asked, ^c4c"what happened to you Pike?"

	^c6fPike responded, ^c4c"Call me Devil Eyes." ^c6fAfter that, Devil Eyes unsheathed 
a silver ritualistic blade and stabbed it deep into his brother's heart. Darkness 
cloaked Sartana's eyes as death enveloped him in its abysmal grasp.  There was no 
telling what lied ahead ...  

^P
^cbbGAME BASICS

^c7dCOMBAT
^c6fThe enemies you face will stop at nothing to hurl you back into the grave whence 
you came, so you'll need to familiarize yourself with your surroundings as well as 
each weapon in your arsenal (including inventory items as they can be very useful 
for getting you out of sticky situations). Hiding behind walls and knowing which 
weapon to use in any given situation can save your unlife. 

^P
^cbbGAME BASICS		(cont'd.)

^cccHelpful Advice: ^c6fUsing a weapon's alt fire indiscriminately can be fun, but 
also eats through your ammo very quickly (especially with weapons where the alt fire 
makes the weapon shoot faster). It is best to use a weapon's alt fire only in situations 
that call for it.

^P
^cbbGAME BASICS		(cont'd.)

^c7dDOORS
^c6fSome doors (such as locked doors) are imbued with magical properties that make 
them shut automatically for inexplicable reasons. It is a good idea to shut doors 
as some enemies (like zombies) are too stupid to open them. 

^P
^cbbGAME BASICS		(cont'd.)

^c7dEXPLORATION & SECRETS
^c6fThe Island of the Shadow is full of areas not easily found. Thorough exploration 
can lead you to areas that contain treasures, useful trinkets, and weapons that you 
would only find later in the game. There are also many walls that can be pushed back, 
either manually or via switch, to reveal secret areas (press the 'use' key to push 
a wall or access switches).

^P
^cbbINFERNAL POWERS

^c6fReturning from the dead not only made Sartana stronger than ever but also granted 
him unholy powers from the other side. Some of these powers fall under the category 
of tertiary attacks. Tertiary attacks can used while armed with weapons.

^P
^cbbINFERNAL POWERS	(cont'd.)  

^cccBEAST VISION: ^c6fBeast vision illuminates your foes in the darkness, making 
them easier to see. Press `B` to activate/deactivate beast vision. Once you acquire 
a crystal ball, your beast vision has the ability to reveal secrets.

^P
^cbbINFERNAL POWERS	(cont'd.) 

^cccMIGHTY KICK: ^c6fThe fact that Sartana can kill his enemies by bludgeoning them 
with his fists is a testament to his unnatural physical strength.  Sartana can also 
kick the shit out of his enemies (it is a much slower attack but it deals more damage 
than punching).  The mighty kick is the first of two tertiary attacks; it can be 
used while equipped with weapons. Press `F` or the middle mouse button to use this 
attack.

^P
^cbbINFERNAL POWERS	(cont'd.)

^cccDEMON EYES: ^c6fUsing this ability, Sartana can also emit a fiery stream of death 
from the windows of his soul. However, unlike Beast Vision, this power is not innate 
and must be earned. This is the second tertiary attack; it also can be used while 
equipped with weapons. Press `F` or the middle mouse button to use this power once 
it becomes available.  Press `Backspace` to toggle between Mighty Kick and Demon 
Eyes.

^P
^cbbINFERNAL POWERS	(cont'd.)

^cccDEMON HANDS: ^c6fThis is the ultimate power. Once acquired, Sartana`s hands are 
possessed with the power to unleash the wrath of hell upon his rivals. When selected 
(press `8` to use), the primary attack lets loose a stream of lightning and the secondary 
attack summons a horde of ghastly spirits capable of eliminating large numbers of 
enemies or bringing down even the hardiest of champions. Additionally, these spirits 
also transfer the target’s life force to the summoner.

^P
^cbbITEMS

^c6fThere are various items that will aid you on your quest. Some items can be used 
as needed (inventory items) while others will be activated the moment you pick them 
up and will wear off after an elapsed amount of time.

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d LIFE ITEMS
^cccBlood Pools: ^c6fRaises your life by 5 points, up to 100.

^cccBlood Vials: ^c6fRaises your life by 10 points, up to 100.

^cccEntrails: ^c6fRaises your life by 15 points, up to 100.

^cccHeart: ^c6fRaises your life by 25 points, up to 100.

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7dARMOR ITEMS
^cccProtection Runes: ^c6fGives you 5 points of armor, up to 100.

^cccLeather Armor: ^c6fGives you 50 points of armor, up 100.

^cccPlated Armor: ^c6fGives you 200 points of armor.

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d TREASURE
^cccMoney Bag: ^c6fAdds 100 points to your score.

^cccSilver Bullion: ^c6fAdds 250 points to your score.

^cccGold Bullion: ^c6fAdds 500 points to your score.

^cccTreasure Chest: ^c6fAdds 1000 points to your score. Additionally, collecting 
10 treasure chests gives you additional bonuses.

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d POWER UPS
^cccWards: ^c6fGives you an additional ward. Wards revitalize you when your life 
falls to 0. Be warned... once you run out of wards and your life reaches 0, final 
death awaits you.

^cccCloak of Protection: ^c6fRegenerates Armor and grants user with superhuman resistance 
to injury, lasts for 120 seconds.

^cccRage Artifact: ^c6fEnhances both movement speed and attack speed, lasts for 45 
seconds.   

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d POWER UPS
^cccBeacon of Unholy: ^c6fMakes you invulnerable, lasts for 30 seconds.

^cccBloodstone: ^c6fGives you a 100 point boost to your life, up to 200 total.

^cccImprisoned Soul: ^c6fGives you 200 life points. 

^cccDemon Skull: ^c6fFuels your Demon Eyes power.

^cccBerserk Mask: ^c6fRegenerates life & boosts melee damage, 90 seconds.  

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d INVENTORY ITEMS 
^cccSilver Daggers: ^c6fThese are good for killing a particularly troublesome enemy 
(most enemies go down with 1 or 2 daggers). They are also good for dispatching enemies 
quietly from a distance.
   
^cccBook of the Dead: ^c6fSummons hordes of wraiths that destroy anything in your 
path. Good for taking out large numbers of enemies.

^cccLife Serum: ^c6fGives you 50 life points.

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d INVENTORY ITEMS
^cccPoppet: ^c6fThis unique item temporarily paralyzes your foes. This item is especially 
useful against fast-moving enemies (executioners, werewolves...)

^cccInfernal Scroll: ^c6fSummons a ball of fire straight from the depths of hell. 
Good for obliterating large clusters of lesser enemies or taking down a particularly 
tough foe.

^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d OTHER ITEMS
^cccCrystal Ball: ^c6fReveals secrets for current level when beast vision is activated.


^cccTomes of knowledge: ^c6fTomes contain bits of helpful wisdom. Read them to gain 
valuable insight.

^cccDybbuk Box: ^c6fMaxes out your inventory supply of poppets and silver daggers.


^P
^cbbITEMS		(cont'd.)

^c7d OTHER ITEMS
^cccTeleportation Artifact: ^c6fThese mystical orbs have the power to transport you 
to distant areas with ease.

^cccKeys: ^c6fEnemies aren't the only things hindering your progress. Apparatuses 
called locked doors can be a major source of frustration. To conquer these foes, 
you need keys. There are four different keys: Gold, Red, Blue, and Green.
 
^P
^cbbWEAPONS

^c6fThe denizens of Shadow Island all have one common goal: to kill you. In order 
to prevent them from succeeding, you will need to gather up an arsenal of death-dealing 
instruments. Most weapons have a primary attack and a secondary attack.

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccFists
^c6fYou begin your quest armed with only your fists. How could you not? They are 
attached to you (for the moment). Once you acquire a more competent weapon, you won't 
be using your fists much... unless you have a death wish.  

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccMachete 
^c6fA large heavy knife with a broad blade that can be very effective if you can 
get it between you and your foes. The most wonderful thing about the machete is its 
ability to maim and dismember. Enemies that fall to your blade almost always die 
with a part (or parts) of their anatomy missing. 

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccPeacemaker 
^c6fAn accurate single action revolver that packs a decent punch. It can shoot faster, 
though less accurately, by fanning the hammer. The peacemaker is probably one of 
the most versatile weapons in the game and is a favorite among many gunslingers. 
The main drawback is its tedious reloading process as bullets have to be loaded individually.

^cccAccuracy: ^c6fVery Good
^cccPower: ^c6fGood
^cccSpeed: ^c6fAverage

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccFrontier 
^c6fA double action revolver made by two close friends of yours: Smith and Wesson. 
This quick-shooter might not be as powerful or as accurate as the peacemaker, but 
it makes up for it with its speed. Additionally, the weapon's top break mechanism 
allows for the utilization of a speed loader which makes reloading much quicker.

^cccAccuracy: ^c6fGood
^cccPower: ^c6fAverage
^cccSpeed: ^c6fVery Good

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccRainmakers
^c6fIncredibly fast-shooting swing-out-cylinder revolvers that have been modified 
to carry double the ammo capacity of a regular revolver. The Rainmakers are very 
handy in tight situations, and when used with a Rage Sphere activated you can easily 
clear a room with these twin brothers.
^cccAccuracy: ^c6fAverage
^cccPower: ^c6fPoor
^cccSpeed: ^c6fExcellent

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccBoomstick
^c6fThe Boomstick is a very reliable ally indeed. It may lack a lot of accuracy, 
but you aren't using a double-barrel shotgun for accuracy now are you!? This weapon 
can be fired either one barrel at a time or both at once for maximum damage.
^cccAccuracy: ^c6fUgly
^cccPower: ^c6fVery Ugly
^cccSpeed: ^c6fPoor

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccThe Savage
^c6fThe Boomstick's bigger, badder brother. This semi-auto beast will hurl your foes 
into an early grave with relative ease. Though it deals quite a wallop and can carry 
more ammo than its double-barrelled brother, reloading this weapon is slow and cumbersome. 

^cccAccuracy: ^c6fPoor
^cccPower: ^c6fExcellent 
^cccSpeed: ^c6fPoor

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccThe Rectifier
^c6fThis fast, high capacity repeater carbine is probably the most well-balanced 
firearm in your arsenal. It is an ideal weapon for disposing of lesser enemies. 

^cccAccuracy: ^c6fVery Good
^cccPower: ^c6fGood
^cccSpeed: ^c6fVery Good

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccThe Reaper
^c6fA powerful repeater carbine that shoots high caliber silver bullets. It is more 
powerful and slightly more accurate than The Rectifier. Great for wiping out more 
powerful foes, especially those pesky werewolves.
^cccAccuracy: ^c6fExcellent
^cccPower: ^c6fVery Good
^cccSpeed: ^c6fGood

^P
^cbbWEAPONS		(cont'd.)

^cccDevil's Mule
^c6fThis mule doesn't like it when people are laughing. He gets the funny feeling 
they are laughing at him. Well... they won't be laughing very long when the trigger 
is pulled. One shot from this monster turns even the hardiest beasts inside out.

^cccAccuracy: ^c6fExcellent
^cccPower: ^c6fTurns foes inside out
^cccSpeed: ^c6fVery Poor

